caption: Good food, service, and atmosphere.

Great food, wine, and service.
New favorite date place ❤
I ate at a nearby park, which allowed my order to soak in a bit on the drive since it wasn't the field right across the street. Once I opened my cheesesteak I was quite impressed.
Our server Kaylee was very welcoming and her service wonderful. Amazing food.. Delicious wonderfully tasting homemade pasta. Will definitely be returning
Amazing pasta and appetizers,  would recommend pasta options over entree dishes as their house made pasta is unbelievably delicious!

This is the best restaurant in Iowa City. While we love to celebrate any special occasion with Baroncini because the food is so delicious, the pricing makes it a great option for any night out. The chef is incredibly talented, you can tell he loves what he does. The food is always made with such wonderful and fresh ingredients. They have an excellent wine list and the waitstaff is always very professional and well versed on the menu. The restaurant itself is small and makes for a fun and intimate dinner.  I always recommend this place to anyone looking for a delicious meal or fun date night.
Great food romantic place
Arianna had multiple interruptions with phone calls and delivery drivers tonight and still managed to make our stop feel personalized and individual. She has wonderful attention to detail. A++
Absolute favorite place in Scottsdale and we visited many restaurants! Food was delicious, environment was amazing, waitresses were quick, friendly and attentive. A must try!
Made from scratch pasta is great
My favorite thing to do is go somewhere beautiful and get something to eat with a glass of wine and a good book, and I saw a woman doing just that here.
italian food at this spot - very good. Do yourself a favor and try this place. It has a cool feel to it. If it wasn't far from my work I would come by more.
Amazing food

I made reservations for 9/17/2020 for my boyfriend & I for our anniversary. The food was absolutely delicious! This is, hands down, the best restaurant we have been to. Everything, from the bread at the beginning to our entrees to our desserts, was perfect. Also, we received great service & the atmosphere of the restaurant was perfect for a romantic dinner. I 100% recommend this place for anyone looking for some authentic, delicious Italian food!
Amazing places. Food taste really delicious 😋.
Food was OK. I wouldn't give it 5 stars. Service was very good though
We happened upon this restaurant while visiting Iowa City and had a fantastic meal.  Love the interesting menu and was impressed by the wine list.
The food is amazing.  Service is fantastic.
Fabulous, sophisticated food, beautifully served.  My partner and I consider it the best restaurant in town!
Friendly service and excellent food. Off-street parking was hard to find so if you make reservations, give yourself extra time to find parking.
An absolute exquisite dining experience 🤩
Baroncini's food is always exceptional,  with service to match. We try to eat here whenever we stay in Iowa City. Can't recommend it strongly enough!

We ate at Baroncini Ristorante Italiano on New Year's Eve. The restaurant had a special four course option for the evening or you could order from the standard menu. My husband chose the four course and I ordered from the standard menu (apetizer, pasta, dessert). Our food was excellent. All dishes were beautifully plated, excellent flavor, and portions were nice as well. Prices were well within reason for the quality of the food.  Unfortunately, we were unluckily assigned to a horrible waiter and seated next to two of his friends that were dining right next to us. The waiter spent more time with his friends chatting, taking sips from their cocktails, and taking selfies with them than attending to others dining in his section. He told us he'd return with more bread but never brought it. I sat with an empty water glass (my only drink) during dessert. He never once checked in on us during any of our courses to see if we were okay or needed anything.  He was very immature and unprofessional as we had to listen to him discuss with his friends about trying to get another wait staff to take his section so he could leave early for New Year's Eve.  I want to love this restaurant because the food is excellent but I'm not sure I can handle returning a second time to be disappointed by another bad waitstaff experience.
Atmosphere was nice. Portions were very small for the cost. Ran out of water twice. Staff was nice.
Upscale dining downtown. Excellent food, very attentive service. $10 lunch special is a great deal.

Upon arrival, I found the lack of a host station confusing. In its place... a coat rack that created quite the traffic jam with people trying to put their coats on while others were trying to enter and exit the restaurant. Pretty awkward layout decision, though slightly understandable given that Baroncini is a smallish place. Right away the host sat us and brought us waters. In fact the service was excellent from start to finish( that concludes all of the good things I can say about my experience at Baroncini) . Which brings me to the food; the food was simply a travesty. Like most Italian restaurants the meal starts with a basket of bread and some olive oil with cracked pepper. I cannot stress how disappointing this bread was. Stale and crumbling with no distinguishing flavor other than flour, this bread was on par with something you might find marked down at a local Cub Foods or HyVee. Truly a bad omen for an Italian restaurant of all places. For our appetizer we ordered a simple caprese bruschetta which wasn’t good but was by far the best tasting thing we had all night. Again the bread was questionable. Three thin, floppy bruschettas with melted mozzarella and halved cherry tomatoes, olive oil and some basaltic reduction. In all my life I don’t think I’ve had such a floppy bruschetta, not appetizing and honestly, very wimpy. Next we had two simple house salads, which aside from the scallops were the grossest dishes of the evening . The lettuce was not fresh and the bits of carrot added a wetness that no one ever wants. Strange decision to add a heap of what tasted like canned chickpeas on top. The salad also had a few cherry tomatoes that looked and tasted like someone sliced them the previous day (they had that pale, gelatinous quality that tomatoes get when cut open and left to absorb the fridge air, you may have had a salad like this at the airport for example). Finally, the entrees, which we waited for approximately 20 mins. When they arrived the plates were hot on top which typically indicates that our food had been sitting under heat lamps for some time. Not a great sign. We ordered the linguini and the scallops. The linguini pasta was actually pretty good, nice texture and felt homemade. I would have found the linguini quite tasty if it had not been salted to death and the shrimp not over cooked. I needed my water refilled mid dish due to the epic salt levels. Sad really. Next the scallops. Typically the quality of a scallop dish comes down to not over or under cooking them. These scallops were basically raw. Surprisingly that didn’t bother me as much as the flavorless butternut squash purée on top of an even more flavorless leek (I think?) purée. We each had three or four bites and that was all me could muster. Determined to end our experience on a positive note, we ordered dessert. We chose the panna cotta. In retrospect we should have ordered a more fool proof dessert but.... we didn’t. The panna cotta was essentially white jello with a raspberry drizzle and whip cream. It’s perhaps unfair to say it was like jello when only the top three quarters was jello-like( or an undercooked scallop..) the very bottom portion had that creamy texture you look for in a good pana cotta. The total cost of the meal was approximately $120 for two very disappointed people. In conclusion, the service was excellent and the food was an utter failure. I would go as far as to say the kitchen staff did an adequate job executing what I would call very bad recipes. Sadly I will not be returning to Baroncini though I wish them the best and hope the menu sees BIG changes soon.

A delicious appetizer was followed by disappointingly average entrees, which was a first for us at Baroncini. Not the restaurant’s fault, but a large, noisy  group seated across from us  made conversation challenging at times. Sadly, we will not return.

Amateurish at best - the bruschetta was floppy if that says anything...great service ! Very attentive. Entrees took a super long time and the bread was doughy and the mixed green salad was flavorless !
Great meal this evening.
Food not worth the price.

Amazing, amazing, amazing. Cannot say enough wonderful things about this restaurant. Owner, entire staff, even the chef comes over and filled our wine glasses twice on the house. Osso bucco as good as it gets anywhere. This is our favorite place we come to every Fri. Or Sat. Night.
Good food!

The experience here was very marginal for the high price.  We were seated at a back table with wine bottles right at head height.  After searching for the wine we ordered, the server determined they were out of it.  There is a coat rack in the way of the entrance and no host station at the front.  Instead the "host station" was directly next to our table, so the host was on the phone taking reservations which frequently interrupted our conversations.  The food was so so, I found the pasta with truffle cream sauce to be largely tasteless and no salt or pepper on the table to adjust flavor.  The chocolate "discs" dessert had a very unappealing texture.  To garner these prices, I believe the restaurant should up their game--including adding touches like fancy soap in the bathroom (not Method), cleaning the top of the bathroom garbage can, and rearranging seating/host station to improve comfort for guests.
the pasta is fantastic.
Excellent!

The best Italian restaurant in who knows how many miles. Delicious home made Italian dishes like your nonna (grandma) would make. There are also changes being made to the menu from time to time so there is always something new to try. The consistent high quality, beautiful presentation and excellent service speak by themselves: the owner/chef has a huge commitment to maintain high standards. It is a lovely place for a date but also to go with family or friends. We have even taken our two little ones and it worked out perfectly!
Wonderful service amazing food.

Food and wine were excellent. The servers are not experienced in wines or attentive. I will go back! The wine selection is spectacular but the waiters are clueless about there detail sommelier is most needed!!!
I went there for lunch and the food was not good at all. I got ravioli and it was tasteless.
Great Homemade Italian foods, nice wines and desserts..
When Chef Baroncini is in the kitchen, this is possibly the only real fine dining in all of Iowa City. You would think you would find him in Italy or  Manhattan ... Rare for downtown Iowa City!
Very nice place to enjoy the food with fantastic service! The price is little but it is worthy！
Food was good. Service wasnt.
Consistently good.
Nice little Italian restaurant. Attentive if somewhat clumsy service.food was excellant.
Dined here three times and it just gets better. Black pasta with shrimp. Fabulous.
Outstanding food. Amazing lunch value. Knowledgeable staff. Pictures of Sophia Loren.
Incredible food. Very good service!
Amazing pasta dishes!!
I have never once had a disappointing meal here.
Butternut squash soup is phenomenal. Great lunch special.
Not too far from home and always good food. You can’t go wrong! Even my husband likes this restaurant. I can’t say that too often. Superb service and food. Always a first choice for me.

Good food and dessert choices

Came here to celebrate finding out the gender of our baby today and they really made it a special experience for me and my boyfriend. The food was fantastic as always. Our server, Cohen, was fantastic!! She was extremely personable and helped to make our night so special. Thank you Baroncini for helping make a special day even more special.

Nice quiet place great service it was very nice not feeling rushed. Every meal was prepared with beautiful presentation, hats off to the chief flavorful not overly seasoned true perfection. Our waitress was as lovely as the food. Highly recommend treating yourself or loved ones

Great little authentic Italian restaurant. Wonderful - and long - Italian wine list. The pastas are fresh and the service is great. I recommend a reservation and plan on a leisurely meal.
Everything was simply incredible. Fresh Italian food, hand made, with a variety and very mature cooking. I loved this food.
Real deal!  No doubt about it.  I lived near Verona Italy for some years...... to get any more authentic you would have to be in the Veneto.  One problem, the price here is sufficiently exaggerated.
The food was just okay.  I was expecting better given the positive reviews and the price point.  They were hilariously running low on clean silverware the night when we went.

The only drawback was that there should have been the white tablecloths as advertised...would give it that touch of class that was sorely lacking....personalized service was some of the best ever...the fact that the chef came out to talk with us was the icing on the cake...the food was incredible...especially the smoke salmon appetizer.
Iowa city hidden gem.  Perfect date night spot.
Good Italian food

I came with a group from work, like we do every year in mid-December. Overall, food is high quality and is served up to look very classy and at a speed to help you enjoy time with good company. It is a small place, and gets cramped when they are busy.  Although I try to be accommodating and patient, I did not feel welcome here as a vegan. I was told the only vegan option was a bowl of elbow noodles with marinara sauce. I asked them to mix in some vegetables for more flavor, but when the dish arrived it was missing the vegetables and had so much excess salt, that is was inedible. While I waited for a new dish, I was not offered anything to snack on. My colleagues all finished their meals before I was given a corrected dish. When it did arrive, it was not at all filling and it looked like a kid's meal next to the elegant dishes of my coworkers. This while experience was frustrating and disappointing.
Fake food, real chef. I don't trust it
Would not recommend going there if you don't have a couple hours to enjoy the meal.  We were there over an hour and still had not received our soup.

I am still thinking about the pasta they served here! Even our son's spaghetti with meatballs dish was amazing- the sauce/noodles were incredibly flavorful. I had a delicious ravioli dish while my husband had the salmon. It is a small/intimate venue. I haven't had pasta that has left such an impression on me in a long time
Excellent food in a cozy space. They deliver every time. Perfect for a date night
Food is really good but the place is too congested
Food was delicious, staff extremely polite. Nice atmosphere.
The food was soooooooo good
Food was spectacular and it changes frequently enough to keep it fresh. Great place to take a date.

Treated myself to salmon pasta and salad takeout after a long day but knew I require extra sauce which I ordered and it was forgotten. Called in to see if I had been charged, which I hadn't and only offered if I wanted to drive back and get it which didn't help me when I was already home & tired. Salmon was good, but for $30 I expected to get what I had ordered.
Outstanding value and excellent cuisine
Food was above average. Good selection of wine. Restaurant was very noisy and we could barely hear each other. We had a reservation but they made use wait at the bar despite open tables on the patio.
Excellent Italian food, coming from a guy who has lived in Italy for 5 years

We waited 45 minutes and never did see our soup or salad materialize, much less, our entrees. Instead we watched our server bring an entire meal, to a gentleman who arrived well AFTER us. It was just two of us. And although the waitress was apologetic, she did not even attempt to give an explanation for why we had not yet received our meals after such a long wait. We ended up having to leave, I had to get back to work, still hungry. We went on a Friday over the lunch hour and ordered off of their lunch menu. How long does it take to put soup into a bowl or throw a salad together?!?!? Apparently TOO long for this place.

I was served after a larger party that arrived later than me. I was handed off between 3 different people on the wait staff, including the bartender. They weren't even busy. Not taken seriously at all. Because of my age, I assume they thought they'd be getting a bad tip anyway. I lose my appetite when people who make minimum wage assume the same of myself. The flavor was good. Portions we're small for my taste. Towellets in the bathroom we're a nice touch, but not nearly enough to make me overlook my unpleasant experience.Olive garden can do better.
Rich, savory, and delicious. The food is so good!
average restaurant . definitely not bad
Their Angnolotti di Carne is one of the best meals I've ever eaten.
Great food, great service, great price

Very nice place with EXCELLENT food! Easy & convenient to find & the staff was very good. A little pricey but well-worth it! They also have a nice lunch menu that is more price-friendly! I had the bone-in Pork Chop with potatoes covered in mushrooms. It was HUGE & fed filled me up with plenty leftover for lunch the next day. Overall, very good!

I would like to say something positive about the food, but nothing comes to mind.... The lobster special was drowned in a red sauce, a failed attempt at a seafood dish.... and the lasagna had a mushy texture similar to a cheap canned ravioli.... Horrible!!! Not worth the money.... Too many other good restaurants in Iowa City to waste your money here

Our friends took us to Baroncini's to celebrate closing on a new house. The food was excellent and filled with a variety of herbs and spices that made it "pop" with flavor. A week later we went back to celebrate our anniversary because we wanted to try other items on the menu we had to pass-up the week before. We were not disappointed. Size-wise this is one of the smaller restaurants in Iowa City, reminiscent of big city and European restaurants. Cozy and not overly loud, a wonderful experience.
Delicious!

Lunch special is fun. For $10 you get an adequate amount of food but it’s mostly salad and bread. Also our food took a while and by the time it came out the noodles were lukewarm or even cold in some places.  Also some orders have way more food on them then others. If you wanna fill up get the spaghetti and meatballs (though you might feel a bit basic). If you’re on a diet the lobster ravioli will do just fine.
Quality fresh made pasta.
I am gluten free and they have gluten free pasta! Lunch was delicious and a great price, plenty of gluten free dishes. I will be back!

Really mixed experience. Very slow service for relatively simple pasta dishes. The burrata was good. A truffle tagliolini was flavorful although luke warm upon arrival. The meat ravioli in sage was unpleasant, overly salty and almost no detectable flavor of sage.
Relatively high priced.  Average service, at best.  Small quantity.  Relatively tasteless food.  Overall, can not recommend.

We went for the lunch special of $10.  Great food. Loved the warm bread. You can chose between the soup and the salad. The salad was fresh. The we were advised by the server to not order the soup as it was a bit old.
Amazing Flavors! Small to medium plate sizes. It is a very cozy place. They are frequently booked until 9 or 930pm. Call a day or two ahead for reservations if you don't plan on eating late.
Chef Gianluca is wonderful.  His pasta is from scratch and you can tell!  He is inventive, authentic, and delicious.  You can buy his lasagna and handmade pasta in the freezer section at New Pi!
Great lunch special. Unfortunately they were out of the dish I really wanted to try.

While it took several minutes(10+) to get a server to the table... the food was amazing and more than made up for the rough start.  A cozy place to enjoy a great meal and look forward to return visits to celebrate additional special occasions.

It’s not often I eat at a place and order an entree that I can’t pronounce but last nights visit to Baroncini Ristorante Italiano just changed that. I can’t believe its been there for 6 years and I’ve just now heard of it. If you haven't; either you need to try it. Immediately upon entry the decor was warm and inviting, elegant without being stuffy. I guess you could even say romantic. We were greeted warmly and throughout the evening our service was spectacular. I just love an engaged and knowledgeable wait staff. It’s not often a salad makes one of my reviews because if a salad is not included with my meal I usually don’t order one. Theirs was not and my wife wanted to try one so we ordered their panzanella salad Traditional Italian bread salad with bread, tomato, onion, spinach, extra virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar and basil. I know salads are usually “light” even with the bread it was super light and refreshing. It has now joined the list of just two or three places  that I can think of I’ll make an exception for where I will order a salad. Usually when I try a new restaurant I rely heavily on the recommendation of the staff and when for I asked our server what they were known and what was her favorite the first thing out of her mouth was the ANGNOLOTTI DI CARNE now I still can't pronounce it but she was able to roll it off her lips like she grew up in Italy my reply was I’ll have what she said. It consisted of  a house made agnolotti pasta stuffed with beef and parmesan in a light sage and brown butter sauce. She had me at brown butter surprisingly it was the hint of sage that was the star of the dish. I was able to steal a few bites of my wife’s  LASAGNE ALLA BOLOGNESE  which was like no other Lasagne I’ve ever had as it had a crunchy panko type topping which provided a textural difference rarely found in a lasagne. I always get excited when a review contains the words “I had the best ever” Baroncini Ristorante Italiano’s TORTA AL MASCARPONE cheesecake is hands down the best cheesecake I’ve ever had. It was the perfect balance of tart and sweet. Caramelizing the mascarpone was absolutely brilliant, it was like the most decadent creme brulee you’ll ever meet or eat but it was cheesecake! The fresh berries and strawberry sauce added a freshness to this amazing dessert. The meals I remember the most are the ones where my stomach is just plain happy afterwards and mine was happy for hours after leaving Baroncini Ristorante Italiano. I think I also had a restaurant first as when we were leaving one of the staff said ciao!  We can't’ wait to return, if for nothing else the mascarpone cheese cake

We love Baroncini for its quiet elegance, delicious meals, informative & friendly wait staff, wine list and the DESSERTS.  Can't forget about the amazing desserts and sometimes go there just for that after a show at the Englert!  We recommend this place to people all the time.

An out-of-towner who stumbled upon this gem while traveling on business. I would describe Baroncini as authentic, intimate, and delicious. The food comes at a price, but really was excellent. I enjoyed the Ravioli Ricotta e Spinaci. I sat at the bar, where the service was excellent, and took advantage of their happy hour (5-630), which got me a dollar off my Peroni. All around an excellent meal and environment.
Great food, wonderful atmosphere, and the service was fantastic.
Fabulous meal and great service@
great food
Holy hell... This place is amazing... The food was sooo good... Staff was super friendly and accommodating! We will definitely be back... One of the top Italian restaurants I've ever eaten at!
Overrated.  Maybe I picked the wrong night. Pasta quality was meh at best.  Like worse than Olive Garden meh.
So amazing! Food, service, setting; everything about this restaurant is amazing
Overpriced and underwhelming.... Much better Italian bistros you could try in Iowa City.

The food was good, the waitress was very knowledgeable about the wines my friend was asking about. My only complaint would be that it's expensive, and it kind of fit into that vibe of Iowa city where it's just kind of pretentious. It reminded me of Clinton Street Social club in terms of vibe. Nice place though, just maybe not my style.  I got the ravioli. It was really good. I was starving when I went in and sometimes places like this, you'll get 5 small pieces and you're dying of hunger still. These were decent size and satisfied me. I wasn't overly stuffed, but wasn't disappointed in the amount of food I got.
It is a wonderful and intimate restaurant with great attention to detail. We shall return and recommend it to friends and family.
Excellent preparations with fresh ingredients. Small cozy atmosphere. A bit pricey.
A nice place with a very reasonably priced lunch menu. The seafood chowder was actually salmon chowder, but the pasta is good and fresh.
Wonderful food, my favorite Italian place in town!

The best local source of Via Veneto/Veronese/Venitian style cuisine, as well as other Northern Italian options.Amazing chef, wonderful staff and fabulous menu. A true gem. Call ahead for special delights and reservations. Really worth it! My go to favorite! Keep up the great work Gianluca! 👌💗😘🇮🇹
A very special place, outstanding service and the best italian food! Found it by Google maps but will be back
Pasta is good
Amazing Lasagna and angel hair past!! It is totally the real mommy's cooking!

Food was great, beautifully presented, owner very pleasant as he checked in with us. Service incredibly slow. Waiter pretentious. Very loud, more like a bar than a nice restaurant. And there was a table of extraordinarily loud guys, one of whom sounded like a braying mule when he howled with laughter, which was often. An impressive wine list, but the one we chose was sold out. The service was so slow that the appetizer we wanted was sold out by the time the waiter came to take our order. Doubt we'll be back.
Fantastic food, service, atmosphere and experience. It's so great to have a place like this in Iowa City. We save it for special occasions because otherwise we would be there every week!
Amazing food, classy atmosphere!

We have loved everything we've tried here--the octopus and crab cake appetizers, cannelloni pasta, tiramisu and bread pudding dessert..though a bit pricey, this is our favorite restaurant in Iowa City! The atmosphere and service are wonderful. Perfect place for a date night!
Great pasta, meat execution/cooking inconsistent
Wonderful place for lunch. Food is simple and light for Italian, and wonderful done. Great wine selection and food is very reasonable priced.
I love this place
Awesome meal.They are so accommodating and hospitable!

wife had scallops small portion  very good appetizer salmon I had aged hanger steak which probly worst cut meat I ever had I had a piece of grizzle between every tooth very expensive  for poor quality meat
Nice vegan options.
Lunch is the best deal
good choices of drink
Fab Italian
Wonderful place to have a meal. Great food, great atmosphere.

Fine Italian dining in Iowa City. The wait staff is very friendly and knowledgable. Everything is made from scratch here and incredible. You can have one or four courses here easily, and you'll want to go back. Very intimate dining area.
Delicious food with attentive service

My boyfriend and I just dined here for our 4 year anniversary. It was an underwhelming and disappointing meal to say the least. I had the seafood chowder to start and it was not salted at all. It was however bearable in contrast to my main course of the scallops and potato risotto. The potatoes were composed mainly of pancetta chunks, making the dish unbelievably salty and inedible. My boyfriend ordered the veal porterhouse which was charred on the outside and raw on the inside. It was almost 90% fat, making his dish inedible as well. On top of that, they charged 30% gratuity for lackluster service. We told them it was our anniversary and they did not bring out anything complimentary or ask if they could do anything special. Needless to say, we will not be returning to this establishment. The food was underwhelming and the prices were exorbitant. Ruined our evening.
Excellent choice for a small group.  Cozy and wonderful food and drinks.  My husband and I enjoy it immensely!
Real Italian cuisine; fresh, & high quality. Nicely stocked bar. Friendly owner and staff!
The best Italian food in town, easily.

Really delicious Italian food with awesome service. Even though this is a pretty fancy/pricey restaurant in the evenings - perfect for celebrating a special event, it has a very reasonably priced lunch menu. The best is the combination menu that they offer. You can get a spectacular meal there for 15 bucks. I think it's the best Italian in Iowa City.

Baroncini is a jewel in Iowa City.  Authentic, tasty, homemade Italian cuisine and the owner and wait staff are always extraordinarily gracious.  One of my favorite spots to dine in IC.  If you want real Italian food, sei arrivato!

I love the personal attention you get at this restaurant! I recently ordered the lobster pasta dish, WOW! So tasty! The menu is always evolving so you can try something new. This is an adult restaurant with adult prices. Love love love!!!
My wife was born and raised in Italy. This is her favorite place in Iowa. Even her foodie parents said this was excellent even with Italian standards.

Our first time in Iowa City brought us here.  We were truly impressed.  Our server recommended a wonderful bottle of wine.  This was THE BEST Italian cuisine we have sampled west of the Mississippi.  The service and food were impeccable. I had the veal chop and my wife took our server's recommendation again and enjoyed the truffles based pasta.  The portion were perfectly sized and this allowed us to enjoy an espresso and some tiramisu.  The owner even stopped by to make sure were happy.  Excellent!
Some of the best Italian I've had.  THE BEST Italian I've has west of the Mississippi.  Pasta was amazing. Buffalo was super tender. Lasagna was just perfect.

Wonderful food, I have eaten there many times and it's always fantastic. So happy to have a restaurant that serves fresh tasty food. The desserts are the best, we go to Baroncini to enjoy excellent wine, food, and chat with friends.

The place has a great boutique atmosphere and a wide selection of wines. I had the lamp chops and wife had lobster.  I was told the lamb chops were served medium rare. When they arrived they were cooked unevenly and tough as heck. The vegetables were cold and over cooked. The lobster was marginal at best, however the pasta was cooked perfectly. This is second time I've eaten here. The service is spotty but well intentioned.

Service was decent and thought the setting was nice. However, the cod fillet I ordered took about 40 minutes to arrive, and happened to be overcooked as well. The lentil-butternut squash portion of the dish didn't do it for me either. For the price, it was definitely not worth it.

I had a spectacular luncheon with Chunghi Choo one of my longest friends in Iowa City this afternoon at Baroncini's.  Smoked salmon with caviar with olive oil and then a delightful dish of linguine with mussels, shrimp, small scallops, calamari and red sauce.  As if that was not more than enough Chunghi, the gracious enabler that she is, ordered an unusual warm flan with spinach and a chocolate mousse with a raspberry sauce at the bottom.  What a treat and a bargain for such a delicious luncheon menu.
Poor service, food was okay but expensive.  Will not be back.

I had the truffle and mushroom fettuccini. The pasta was so overcooked that the entire affair was a large pad of mush on a plate--and a small serving at that. The food took far too long for a single course. On the plus side, the good wine selection almost made the whole experience tolerable.

Delicious, and the menu is such that you can attempt toward a traditional Italian meal with separate pasta course and meat courses. Building is quite small and narrow, so the feel is more like a café than fine dining, but the food is definitely the latter.
Try everything even if you generally wouldn't eat it in a different setting.
